<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> First I will begin by summarizing the quest that one is given from the red dragon Malafen in Western Wastes in regards to Sleeper's Tomb and Kerafyrm; then I will go into the latest in a round of mishaps with Sleeper's Tomb. <br>
<br>
Malafen is a Disciple of Kerafyrm. He is looking for proof of his master's existance/location. The actual proof he seeks is a 'Prismatic Scale,' which is gotten from one of three Boss Golems in Sleeper's Tomb. Along with the scale, he requests that you turn in your Sleeper's Tomb key for a reward. Turning in both the 'Prismatic Scale,' and the 'ST Key,' results in one of five 'Essence Items,' which a player can hand back to Malafen to recycle until they receive the one they want. <br>
<br>
End Result: The player loses both a Sleeper's Tomb key and a RIDICULOUSLY rare Prismatic Scale (We have 1 scale in our guild in some two-three dozen Boss Golem kills) for an 'Essence Item.' <br>
<br>
Now onto the latest mishap. I will preface this with an incident that happened in the first few days of SoV, nearly a year ago. <br>
<br>
When Scars of Vellious first went live, people that ventured into the Skyshrine and killed random cubes were finding 'Clawed Griffin Swords.' This sword is the same reward one gets from Lord Yelinak by handing in King Tormax's head. After two days Verant finally realized what was happening and did a retroactive nerf to ALL 'Clawed Griffin Swords,' (CGS) turning them into 'Dark Swords of Shame,' a completely gimped version of the CGS. This wasn't Sleeper's Tomb end game loot that ALL/ALL could even use - but Verant realized it had made a large mistake and fixed the problem. <br>
<br>
Fast forward to today. <br>
<br>
For the past five days, a guild on our server has been camped in Western Wastes 24/7. Why you ask? Malafen, the same dragon that was mentioned earlier in this post, had a bugged drop. He was dropping 'Essence Lenses.' He was also spawning once every 45 minutes. This guild in question farmed - at LEAST by our estimation, 30-40 of these items. They also knew this was a bugged drop, it had no business dropping off Malafen, but continued to farm the drop. <br>
<br>
Yes folks, a guild with a total of three Sleeper's Tomb keys; a guild that has never seen the inside of Sleeper's Tomb, let alone a boss golem, and DEFINITELY not any of the now extinct warders, is riding high in dozens and dozens of Sleeper's Tomb end game gear. <br>
<br>
We went against better judgement for five days and didn't post a damned THING on this message board because we didn't want to cause this kind of turmoil on other servers, hoping that the GMs we petitioned would act a little faster than dried up slugs. We were wrong. <br>
<br>
It's time to step up Verant. Don't set a bogus precident here - we already have one to go by in an instance like this - Clawed Griffon Swords. Every single 'Essence Item,' at least on Veeshan, should be turned into a 'Fire Beetle Eye.' If you were to ask me, the guild leader of the guild doing the farming should have his account suspended (if not banned) for blatantly farming a bugged drop for FIVE solid days. <br>
<br>
I eagerly await a resolution to this problem.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uurgetakildaogur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Urgetakil da Ogur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/19/01 9:56:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=604.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/_ht_a/jordanzone/ff2/gifs/cecil.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleeper's Tomb bug</span><hr size=1> hahaha <br>
